    Scope and Contents
WWII CONSCIENTIOUS OBJECTORS PROJECT 
Meredith Dallas, jailed Union Seminary WWII conscientious objector, discusses pacifism, his formative experiences, fellow conscientious objectors, his imprisonment in 1940 with eight other Union Seminary students, and his careers in teaching and the theater. Willa and Meredith Dallas discuss civil rights, protests, peace issues, and women's rights. 2 tapes, 239 mins., 55 pp. 
Interview by C. Arthur Bradley, 1988 
